summary: I love how casual Dany fans who don't closely follow the hidden meaning of Dany's story call Dany "Khaleesi", like they...
body: I love how casual Dany fans who don’t closely follow the hidden meaning of Dany’s story call Dany “Khaleesi”, like they subconsciously know that she’s already in a position of power and has been training to be a queen since season one of her journey. Like Dany even exudes so much respect and personality that even viewers, who don’t live in a feudal system and aren’t used to addressing people in titles outside of sir and ma'am, are addressing her through a title that means queen.

summary: I kinda didn’t like how everyone looks so masculine. Sure it’s winter blah blah but I don’t get why all the diversity and...
question: I kinda didn’t like how everyone looks so masculine. Sure it’s winter blah blah but I don’t get why all the diversity and femininity should be taken away from every woman. They all wear alike and masculine now, even Sansa. Also I hate how they still try to sell Dany, everything is Dany-first again. I just can’t wait for this shitshow to be over and the hype of the casual watchers to die.
answer:
The lack of variety stinks. Having colour won’t change the fact that the world ending is serious business. I can’t blame Michelle for this because D&D have made their hatred of femininity obvious. Their idea of Sansa developing is putting her through intense trauma and then having her behave in a cold manner.

Honestly this season’s promo is so Sansa heavy. She was mentioned in the first ever EW article and cover of the season. She was in the first three teasers. Sophie has been doing a lot of interviews. A lot of the speculation is centred around Sansa in the online publications. Everything we see and hear about Dany so far is interesting (thank you Emilia for giving me hope lmao), in that she’s not presented as a hero. There’s a lot of talk about her issues with Sansa especially after the second teaser when it’s obvious how little she’s wanted. The poster has her posing like Euron and the Night King, even Cersei looks softer. In other words anon we’re getting fed better than Dany stans.

body:
Bran & Jon

I’m curious as to how Jon will learn of his true parentage. So far, we’ve seen that Bran, as the 3ER, doesn’t have much tact when it comes to discussing what he’s seen (case in point, when he told Sansa she looked beautiful on the night she married Ramsay)


  • Sam knows the truth, will he help Bran with revealing R+L=J to Jon?
  • Will Sansa & Arya be told the truth before Jon’s arrival so they’ve had time to process and formulate a plan to best help protect him?
  • Will Sansa & Arya learn the truth the same time as Jon?


I just don’t want Bran to be all

“Hello Jon. I’m not Bran, I’m the 3ER. You’re probably wondering why you were having a panic attack mid thrust with D@ny …..well, it’s because she’s your Aunt. You’re not our brother, but our cousin. Lyanna was your mother, she secretly wed Rhaegar.”


Jon: 🤯🤯🤯

summary: I really wish they’d let Sansa and Brienne be actual friends on the show. I feel like they both need a confidant and someone...
question: I really wish they’d let Sansa and Brienne be actual friends on the show. I feel like they both need a confidant and someone they can trust and while they’re obviously very different people, I think they’re also both very kind and genuinely good in a way not a lot of GOT characters are. (Also like… I very much support the idea of Queen Sansa with Brienne as the Lady Commander of her Queensguard.)
answer: I expected it but D&D have a long history of cutting down and erasing female friendships. In the books, Brienne and Catelyn spend time together before Jaime’s release, it’s not necessarily friendship but it’s important. Cersei had a complex friendship with Taena who the show doesn’t bother to introduce. They extend Sansa and Margaery’s interactions but that was only to make Margaery look good to the point removing important aspects of Sansa’s character. Brienne has been stripped of her vulnerability and femininity and now she barely has any relationship with Sansa. D&D could have used both characters to develop the other but no, they put all their effort to make Gendry get along with men who sold him and Tormund making friends the Hound. I’m annoyed.
